President Cyril Ramaphosa announced on Monday night that Nhlanhla Nene would be replacing Malusi Gigaba in the portfolio. CAPE TOWN - The South African Revenue Services (Sars) has welcomed the reappointment of Nhlanhla Nene as finance minister, saying Sars has enjoyed a successful working relationship with him in the past. President Cyril Ramaphosa announced on Monday night that Nene would be replacing Malusi Gigaba in the portfolio. Sars says Nene’s passion for governance will assist the revenue service with efficiency. Spokesperson Sandile Memela says: “There is no doubt that his leadership will further galvanise the Sars workforce and boost the morale in the challenging economic environment.”    (Edited by Shimoney Regter)